%U A084817 3522801366,9932925036,28006972162,78968731457,222661004264,627817136045,1770199310902,4991271216425
%N A084817 Least integers that satisfy Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n)^z = 0, where a(1)=1, a(n+1)>a(n) and z=I/log(2).
%C A084817 Sequence satisfies Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n)^z = 0 by requiring that the modulus of the successive partial sums are monotonically decreasing in magnitude for the given z.
%C A084817 |Sum_{k=1..n} 1/a(k)^z| appears to converge geometrically to 0.73530592... Does this behavior continue? If this is true then the complex sum converges to a circular orbit rather than a single value. - _Martin Fuller_, May 24 2026
%o A084817 (PARI) my(z=I/log(2), S=0, w=1, a=0); for(n=1,100,b=a+1; while(abs(S+exp(-z*log(b)))>w,b++); S=S+exp(-z*log(b)); w=abs(S); a=b; print1(b,", "))
%o A084817 (PARI) \\ See Fuller link in A084813
